# Testing Policy

## Always run tests before pushing

```bash
npm run test:run   # must exit 0 before any git push
```

If tests fail, **fix the failures before committing**. Never push with a red test suite.

## When to add or update tests

- Any change to `src/api.js` → update `src/test/api.test.js` or `src/test/core-logic.test.js`
- Any change to profit / P&L calculation logic → update `tradeProfit` tests in `src/test/core-logic.test.js`
- Any new utility function → add a test in the closest existing test file

## Test files

| File | What it covers |
|------|---------------|
| `src/test/api.test.js` | Basic apiClient methods (CRUD, auth) |
| `src/test/api.comprehensive.test.js` | Edge cases, error codes, token flows |
| `src/test/core-logic.test.js` | `isTokenExpired`, 401 event, profit calc, strike display |

## Running tests

```bash
npm run test:run        # single run (CI / pre-push)
npm run test            # watch mode (development)
npm run test:coverage   # coverage report
```

## Pre-push reminder

Before `git push`, always confirm:
```
✓ npm run test:run   → all tests pass
```
